25/05/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Russia's Dima Bilan won the 2008 Eurovision Song Contest on Saturday evening (May 24th), becoming the first Russian champion in the competition's 52-year history. He placed second in 2006. His song, "Believe," received 272 points from voters in 43 countries. 
Ukrainian disco star Ani Lorak took second with 230 points, and Greece's Kalomira ranked third with 218 points. Belgrade hosted the event, since Serbian singer Marija Serifovic won last year. More than 100 million people worldwide watched the competition. (Blic, Politika, Tanjug, RTS, Reuters, CNN, Deutsche Welle - 25/05/08)
